<h2>LOCATION AND DIRECTIONS </h2>
<p>The iSchool is located in the <a href="http://www.utexas.edu/maps/main/buildings/uta.html">UT Administration Building (UTA)</a>, two blocks south of UT's main campus at <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&source=s_q&hl=en&geocode=&q=1616+Guadalupe+St,+Austin,+tx&sll=37.0625,-95.677068&sspn=48.641855,105.292969&ie=UTF8&hq=&hnear=1616+Guadalupe+St,+Austin,+Travis,+Texas+78701&z=17">1616 Guadalupe Street</a>, across the street from the Clay Pit restaurant and Dog & Duck pub.</p>
<img src="images/iSchool_exterior_small.jpg" height="250px"> <img src="images/uta_inset.gif" height="250px"/>
<h2>Walking</h2>
<p>Walking to UTA from the center of campus takes about 10 to 15 minutes. The UTA Building is two blocks south of the main UT campus.</p>
<h2>Biking</h2>
<p>Bike racks can be found on the north side of the building (facing 17th street, pictured to the right).</p>
<h2>Bus</h2>
<p><a href="http://www.utexas.edu/parking/transportation/shuttle/">UT Shuttle service </a>is available via the<a href="http://www.capmetro.org/riding/schedules_ut.asp"> ER or LA shuttles</a>. The building is also accessible via many Capital Metro bus routes, use the <a href="http://www.capmetro.org/planner/">Capital Metro trip planner </a>to check specific routes and times.</p>
<h2>Car</h2>
<p>Paid parking is available in the attached <a href="http://www.utexas.edu/parking/parking/garages/gug.php">GUG garage </a>or on-street via meter parking.</p>
